            <thetext>Under Vista IE7 throws an error when opening a local qooxdoo demo application/page. The error occours is:

A runtime error has occurred.
Do you want to start the debug mode?

Line: 1
Error: Invalid Character</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>1642</commentid>
            <who name="Sebastian Werner">info</who>
            <bug_when>2007-06-26 16:25:42 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Execution of active content is disabled by default in IE7 on Vista. This can be enabled in the advanced options. If disabled the yellow information bar will be shown and ask for acception of dynamic content execution.

If the content will be executed (through the enabled option or through the permission to execute the active content) the mentioned script error occurs.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>1643</commentid>
            <who name="Sebastian Werner">info</who>
            <bug_when>2007-06-26 16:27:45 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>It seems that Microsoft&#39;s new security system has problems with locally non-existing files. I will attach a sample.

This can affect qooxdoo based applications if the includer (source version) is out-of-date through renaming or deletion of included JS files.

I will attach a small example.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
